          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-670 Remove ldiskfs_dirhash from Lustre",
        "message": "LU-670 Remove ldiskfs_dirhash from Lustre\n\nThe ldiskfs_dirhash() function is only used by the ldiskfs osd.\nSince this functionality was originally copied from ldiskfs\nit makes sense to remove it entirely and rely on the ldiskfs\nimplementation.\n\nNormally this symbol isn't exported but since we are already\npatching ldiskfs exporting it for use is trivial.  This is\ncurrently done with the following ldiskfs patch for rhel6.\n\n  ldiskfs/kernel_patches/patches/ext4-osd-iam-exports-rhel6.patch\n\nChange-Id: I9a0ed25e4a2548328d91958608b6870fff7a8f88\nSigned-off-by: Brian Behlendorf <behlendorf1@llnl.gov>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
